Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry all
produce. Peel and cut @Carrots{6} into 1-inch pieces. Dice @Yukon Gold Potatoes{24%ounce}
into 1-inch cubes. Halve and peel @Yellow Onion{1}, then mince until you have
½ cup (use the rest as you like). Finely chop @Parsley{¼%ounce}.

Toss carrots on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @Vegetable Oil{1%tsp}
and a large pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack for ~{15%minutes}
(we'll add more to sheet then). Meanwhile, place potatoes in a #medium pot{} with
a large pinch of salt and enough water to cover by 1 inch. Bring to a boil and
cook until tender, about ~{15%minutes}. Drain and return to empty pot off heat.

In a #large bowl{}, combine @White Bread{2%slice} and 6 TBSP @Milk{13.5%ounce}
(we sent more). Break up bread with your hands until pasty. Thoroughly mix in
@Ground Beef{20%ounce}, half the minced onion, half the parsley, @Nutmeg{¼%tsp},
@Meatloaf Spice Blend{1%tablespoon}, salt, and pepper (we sent more nutmeg;
our chefs used 1 1/2 tsp kosher salt). Shape mixture into four 1-inch-tall loaves.

Heat a large drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add
meatloaves and cook until browned on surface but not yet cooked through, about
~{3%minutes} per side. Once carrots have roasted about 15 minutes, remove sheet
from oven and give carrots a toss. Add meatloaves to same sheet and place in
oven. Bake until meatloaves are cooked through and carrots are tender, about
~{15%minutes} more.

Melt 2 TBSP @Butter{4%tablespoon} in same pan over medium heat. Add remaining
minced onion. Cook, tossing, until soft, about ~{2%minutes}. Add @Flour{2%tablespoon}
and cook, stirring, until pasty, about ~{1%minute}. Slowly whisk in 1 cup
water, followed by @Beef Stock Concentrate{2} and ½ cup milk (save rest for
potatoes). Bring to a simmer, then whisk until thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}. Season
with salt, pepper, and a pinch of nutmeg (to taste).

> TIP: Add more water if too thick.

Place #pot{} with potatoes over low heat. Add 2 TBSP butter and @Milk{½%cup}.
Mash until smooth with #potato masher{}. (TIP: Add more milk if stiff.) Season
with salt and pepper. Divide potatoes and meatloaves between plates. Drizzle
with gravy. Add carrots and @Currant Jam{4%tablespoon} to the side. Garnish with
remaining parsley.